txt.en: DNT

'We march to Gundabad, together. All of us who march, we are all the Gabil'akkâ, the Great Force!

'Are you on your way to Annâk-khurfu? You must be, as the Rushgate is but the start of the march! Could you do something for me on your way to Annâk-khurfu, my friend? I want to lift the spirits of all those in the Gabil'akkâ. Let us raise banners along the path, as it is now under control of the Gabil'akkâ!

'Oh and one more thing. Could you investigate the small encampment of Khadâsh-gâra for me? I am not sure what the dwarves there doing to keep themselves busy!'
Rúzat has asked you to plant banners along the road leading to Annâk-khurfu and to investigate Khadâsh-gâra.\n\nYou should plant banners along the road leading to Annâk-khurfu.
The stronghold is filled with many dwarves from across the lands
'You have assisted everyone at Annâk-khurfu? You always seem to find a way to impress me, [placeholder]! Now then, let us see how your talents might best serve the Gabil'akkâ next.'

'Ah, there you are! What took you so long? Did Rúzat put you to work at the Rushgate? Bah, I knew it. Does he not know that time is of the utmost importance in order for the Gabil'akkâ to succeed?\n\n'Now then, enough idle chatter, there is much to be done here at Annâk-khurfu! I know that I can count on you, [placeholder]. That is why I am giving you these important tasks. Come talk to me again when you have completed them!'
